-1.png 204w, https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-Ideas-Math-Answer-Key-Grade-8-Chapter-4-Graphing-and-Writing-Linear-Equations-1-136x300.png 136w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 204px) 100vw, 204px\" \/><br \/>\n1. Robert says that the closer you are to the eye of a hurricane, the stronger the winds become. The wind speed on an island is 50 miles per hour when the eye of a hurricane is 140 miles away.<br \/>\na. Describe the wind speed on the island when the eye of the hurricane is 100 miles away.<br \/>\nb. Describe the distance of the island from the eye of the hurricane when the wind speed on the island is 25 miles per hour.<br \/>\nc. Sketch a line that could represent the wind speed y (in miles per hour) on the island when the eye of x the hurricane is miles away from the island. Wind speed<br \/>\n2. A storm dissipates as it travels over land. What does this mean?<\/p>\n<p><strong>Performance Task<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Anatomy of a Hurricane<br \/>\nAfter completing this chapter, you will be able to use the concepts you learned to answer the questions in the STEAM Video Performance Task. You will be given information about the atmospheric pressure inside a hurricane.<br \/>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-32968\" src=\"https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-Ideas-Math-Answer-Key-Grade-8-Chapter-4-Graphing-and-Writing-Linear-Equations-2.png\" alt=\"Big Ideas Math Answer Key Grade 8 Chapter 4 Graphing and Writing Linear Equations 2\" width=\"540\" height=\"331\" srcset=\"https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-Ideas-Math-Answer-Key-Grade-8-Chapter-4-Graphing-and-Writing-Linear-Equations-2.png 540w, https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-Ideas-Math-Answer-Key-Grade-8-Chapter-4-Graphing-and-Writing-Linear-Equations-2-300x184.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 540px) 100vw, 540px\" \/><br \/>\nYou will be asked to use a model to find the strength of a hurricane after x hours of monitoring. Why is it helpful to predict how strong the winds of a hurricane will become?<\/p>\n<h3><a id=\"Graphing_and_Writing_Linear_Equations_Getting_Ready_for_Chapter_4\"><\/a>Graphing and Writing Linear Equations Getting Ready for Chapter 4<\/h3>\n<p><strong>Chapter Exploration<\/strong><br \/>\n1. Work with a partner.<br \/>\na. Use the equation y = \\(\\frac{1}{2}\\)x + 1 to complete the table. (Choose any two x-values and find the y-values.)<br \/>\nb. Write the two ordered pairs given by the table. These are called solutions of the equation.<br \/>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-32969\" src=\"https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-Ideas-Math-Answer-Key-Grade-8-Chapter-4-Graphing-and-Writing-Linear-Equations-3.1.png\" alt=\"Big Ideas Math Answer Key Grade 8 Chapter 4 Graphing and Writing Linear Equations 3.1\" width=\"205\" height=\"309\" srcset=\"https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-Ideas-Math-Answer-Key-Grade-8-Chapter-4-Graphing-and-Writing-Linear-Equations-3.1.png 205w, https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-Ideas-Math-Answer-Key-Grade-8-Chapter-4-Graphing-and-Writing-Linear-Equations-3.1-199x300.png 199w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 205px) 100vw, 205px\" \/><br \/>\nc. PRECISION Plot the two solutions. Draw a line exactly through the points.<br \/>\nd. Find a different point on the line. Check that this point is a solution of the equation y = \\(\\frac{1}{2}\\)x + 1.<br \/>\ne. <strong>LOGIC<\/strong> Do you think it is true that any point on the line is a solution of the equation y = \\(\\frac{1}{2}\\)x + 1? Explain.<br \/>\nf. Choose five additional x-values for the table below. (Choose both positive and negative x-values.) Plot the five corresponding solutions. Does each point lie on the line?<br \/>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-32970\" src=\"https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-Ideas-Math-Answer-Key-Grade-8-Chapter-4-Graphing-and-Writing-Linear-Equations-3.png\" alt=\"Big Ideas Math Answer Key Grade 8 Chapter 4 Graphing and Writing Linear Equations 3\" width=\"397\" height=\"98\" srcset=\"https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-Ideas-Math-Answer-Key-Grade-8-Chapter-4-Graphing-and-Writing-Linear-Equations-3.png 397w, https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-Ideas-Math-Answer-Key-Grade-8-Chapter-4-Graphing-and-Writing-Linear-Equations-3-300x74.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 397px) 100vw, 397px\" \/><br \/>\ng.<strong> LOGIC<\/strong> Do you think it is true that any solution of the equation y = \\(\\frac{1}{2}\\)x + 1 is a point on the line? Explain.<br \/>\nh. Why do you think y = ax + b is called a linear equation?<\/p>\n<p>Vocabulary<br \/>\nThe following vocabulary terms are defined in this chapter. Think about what each term might mean and record your thoughts.<br \/>\nlinear equation<br \/>\nslope<br \/>\ny-intercept<br \/>\nsolution of a linear equation<br \/>\nx-intercept<\/p>\n<h3><a id=\"Lesson_4.1_Graphing_Linear_Equations\"><\/a>Lesson 4.1 Graphing Linear Equations<\/h3>\n<p><strong>EXPLORATION 1<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Creating Graphs<br \/>\nWork with a partner. It starts snowing at midnight in Town A and Town B. The snow falls at a rate of 1.5 inche sper hour.<br \/>\na. In Town A, there is no snow on the ground at midnight. How deep is the snow at each hour between midnight and 6 A.M.? Make a graph that represents this situation.<br \/>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-32971\" src=\"https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-Ideas-Math-Answer-Key-Grade-8-Chapter-4-Graphing-and-Writing-Linear-Equations-4.1-1.png\" alt=\"Big Ideas Math Answer Key Grade 8 Chapter 4 Graphing and Writing Linear Equations 4.1 1\" width=\"272\" height=\"261\" \/><br \/>\nb. Repeat part(a) for TownB, which has 4 inches of snow on the ground at midnight.<br \/>\nc. The equations below represent the depth y(in inches) of snow x hours after midnight in Town C and Town D. Graph each equation.<br \/>\nTown C y = 2x + 3<br \/>\nTown D y = 8<br \/>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-32972\" src=\"https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-Ideas-Math-Answer-Key-Grade-8-Chapter-4-Graphing-and-Writing-Linear-Equations-4.1-2.png\" alt=\"Big Ideas Math Answer Key Grade 8 Chapter 4 Graphing and Writing Linear Equations 4.1 2\" width=\"430\" height=\"196\" srcset=\"https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-Ideas-Math-Answer-Key-Grade-8-Chapter-4-Graphing-and-Writing-Linear-Equations-4.1-2.png 430w, https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-Ideas-Math-Answer-Key-Grade-8-Chapter-4-Graphing-and-Writing-Linear-Equations-4.1-2-300x137.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 430px) 100vw, 430px\" \/><br \/>\nd. Use your graphs to compare the snowfall in each town.<br \/>\nAnswer:<\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-32973\" src=\"https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-Ideas-Math-Answer-Key-Grade-8-Chapter-4-Graphing-and-Writing-Linear-Equations-4.1-3.png\" alt=\"Big Ideas Math Answer Key Grade 8 Chapter 4 Graphing and Writing Linear Equations 4.1 3\" width=\"187\" height=\"99\" \/><\/p>\n<p><strong>Try It<\/strong><\/p>\n<p><strong>Graph the linear equation<\/strong>.<br \/>\nQuestion 1.<br \/>\ny = 3x<br \/>\nAnswer:<br \/>\nMake to table of values<br \/>\nReplace x with a number and find the value of y<br \/>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-74795\" src=\"https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-ideas-math-answers-grade-8-chapter-4-img_1-300x155.png\" alt=\"Big ideas math answers grade 8 chapter 4 img_1\" width=\"300\" height=\"155\" srcset=\"https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-ideas-math-answers-grade-8-chapter-4-img_1-300x155.png 300w, https:\/\/ccss