x\" \/><br \/>\nPlot the ordered pairs<br \/>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-74819\" src=\"https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-ideas-math-answers-grade-8-chapter-4-img_3.2-300x195.png\" alt=\"Big ideas math answers grade 8 chapter 4 img_3.2\" width=\"300\" height=\"195\" srcset=\"https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-ideas-math-answers-grade-8-chapter-4-img_3.2-300x195.png 300w, https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-ideas-math-answers-grade-8-chapter-4-img_3.2.png 717w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" \/><\/p>\n<p><strong>Graph the linear equation.<\/strong><br \/>\nQuestion 4.<br \/>\ny = 3<br \/>\nAnswer:<br \/>\nThe graph of y = 3 is a horizontal like passing through (0, 3)<br \/>\nDraw a horizontal line through this point.<br \/>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-74822\" src=\"https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-ideas-math-answer-key-grade-8-chapter-4-img_4-300x250.png\" alt=\"Big ideas math answer key grade 8 chapter 4 img_4\" width=\"300\" height=\"250\" srcset=\"https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-ideas-math-answer-key-grade-8-chapter-4-img_4-300x250.png 300w, https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-ideas-math-answer-key-grade-8-chapter-4-img_4.png 591w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Question 5.<br \/>\ny = &#8211; 1.5<br \/>\nAnswer:<br \/>\nThe graph of y = -1.5 is a horizontal line passing through (0, -1.5)<br \/>\nDraw a horizontal line through this point.<br \/>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-74827\" src=\"https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-ideas-math-answer-key-grade-8-chapter-4-img_5-300x195.png\" alt=\"Big ideas math answer key grade 8 chapter 4 img_5\" width=\"300\" height=\"195\" srcset=\"https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-ideas-math-answer-key-grade-8-chapter-4-img_5-300x195.png 300w, https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-ideas-math-answer-key-grade-8-chapter-4-img_5.png 619w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Question 6.<br \/>\nx = &#8211; 4<br \/>\nAnswer:<br \/>\nThe graph of x = &#8211; 4 is a vertical line passing through (-4, 0)<br \/>\nDraw a vertical line through this point.<br \/>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-74835\" src=\"https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/BIM-Grade-8-Answers-Chapter-4-img_6-300x267.png\" alt=\"BIM Grade 8 Answers Chapter 4 img_6\" width=\"300\" height=\"267\" srcset=\"https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/BIM-Grade-8-Answers-Chapter-4-img_6-300x267.png 300w, https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/BIM-Grade-8-Answers-Chapter-4-img_6.png 419w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Question 7.<br \/>\nx = \\(\\frac{1}{2}\\)<br \/>\nAnswer:<br \/>\nThe graph of x = \\(\\frac{1}{2}\\) is a vertical line passing through (\\(\\frac{1}{2}\\), 0)<br \/>\nDraw a vertical line through this point.<br \/>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-74838\" src=\"https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-Ideas-Math-8th-Grade-Solution-Key-Chapter-4-img_7-300x250.png\" alt=\"Big Ideas Math 8th Grade Solution Key Chapter 4 img_7\" width=\"300\" height=\"250\" srcset=\"https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-Ideas-Math-8th-Grade-Solution-Key-Chapter-4-img_7-300x250.png 300w, https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-Ideas-Math-8th-Grade-Solution-Key-Chapter-4-img_7.png 477w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" \/><\/p>\n<p><strong>Self-Assessment for Concepts &amp; Skills<\/strong><br \/>\nSolve each exercise. Then rate your understanding of the success criteria in your journal.<\/p>\n<p><strong>GRAPHING A LINEAR EQUATION<\/strong> Graph the linear equation.<br \/>\nQuestion 8.<br \/>\ny = &#8211; x + 1<br \/>\nAnswer:<br \/>\nMake of a table of values<br \/>\nReplace x with a number and find the value of y<br \/>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-74842\" src=\"https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-Ideas-Math-8th-Grade-Solution-Key-Chapter-4-img_8.1-300x199.png\" alt=\"Big Ideas Math 8th Grade Solution Key Chapter 4 img_8.1\" width=\"300\" height=\"199\" srcset=\"https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-Ideas-Math-8th-Grade-Solution-Key-Chapter-4-img_8.1-300x199.png 300w, https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-Ideas-Math-8th-Grade-Solution-Key-Chapter-4-img_8.1.png 513w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" \/><br \/>\nPlot the values of x and y obtained, on the graph,<br \/>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-74844\" src=\"https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-Ideas-Math-8th-Grade-Solution-Key-Chapter-4-img_8.2-300x210.png\" alt=\"Big Ideas Math 8th Grade Solution Key Chapter 4 img_8.2\" width=\"300\" height=\"210\" srcset=\"https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-Ideas-Math-8th-Grade-Solution-Key-Chapter-4-img_8.2-300x210.png 300w, https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-Ideas-Math-8th-Grade-Solution-Key-Chapter-4-img_8.2.png 461w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Question 9.<br \/>\ny = 0.8x &#8211; 2<br \/>\nAnswer:<br \/>\nReplace x with a number and find the value of y<br \/>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-74846\" src=\"https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-Ideas-Math-8th-Grade-Solution-Key-Chapter-4-img_9.1-300x204.png\" alt=\"Big Ideas Math 8th Grade Solution Key Chapter 4 img_9.1\" width=\"300\" height=\"204\" srcset=\"https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-Ideas-Math-8th-Grade-Solution-Key-Cha