9.png\" alt=\"BIM Grade 8 Answer Key Chapter 4 img_11\" width=\"300\" height=\"179\" srcset=\"https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/BIM-Grade-8-Answer-Key-Chapter-4-img_11-300x179.png 300w, https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/BIM-Grade-8-Answer-Key-Chapter-4-img_11.png 619w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Question 12.<br \/>\n<strong>WHICH ONE DOESN\u2019T BELONG?<\/strong><br \/>\nWhich equation does not belong with the other three? Explain your reasoning.<br \/>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-32974\" src=\"https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-Ideas-Math-Answer-Key-Grade-8-Chapter-4-Graphing-and-Writing-Linear-Equations-4.1-4.png\" alt=\"Big Ideas Math Answer Key Grade 8 Chapter 4 Graphing and Writing Linear Equations 4.1 4\" width=\"393\" height=\"42\" srcset=\"https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-Ideas-Math-Answer-Key-Grade-8-Chapter-4-Graphing-and-Writing-Linear-Equations-4.1-4.png 393w, https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-Ideas-Math-Answer-Key-Grade-8-Chapter-4-Graphing-and-Writing-Linear-Equations-4.1-4-300x32.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 393px) 100vw, 393px\" \/><br \/>\nAnswer:<br \/>\ny = x &#8211; 2<br \/>\n4x + 3 = y<br \/>\ny = x\u00b2 + 6<br \/>\nx + 5 = y<\/p>\n<p><strong>Self-Assessment for Problem Solving<\/strong><br \/>\nSolve each exercise. The rate your understanding of the success criteria in your journal.<\/p>\n<p>Question 13.<br \/>\nA game show contestant earns y dollars for completing a puzzle in x minutes. This situation is represented by the equation y = &#8211; 250x + 5000. How long did a contestant who earned $500 take to complete the puzzle? Justify your answer.<br \/>\nAnswer:<br \/>\nGiven,<br \/>\nA game show contestant earns y dollars for completing a puzzle in x minutes.<br \/>\nThis situation is represented by the equation y = &#8211; 250x + 5000.<br \/>\ny = -250x + 5000<br \/>\n500 = -250x + 5000<br \/>\n500 &#8211; 5000 = -250x + 5000 &#8211; 5000<br \/>\n-4500 = -250x<br \/>\nx = 18<\/p>\n<p>Question 14.<br \/>\nThe total cost y (in dollars) to join a cheerleading team and attend x competitions is represented by the equation y = 10x + 50.<br \/>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-32975\" src=\"https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-Ideas-Math-Answer-Key-Grade-8-Chapter-4-Graphing-and-Writing-Linear-Equations-4.1-5.png\" alt=\"Big Ideas Math Answer Key Grade 8 Chapter 4 Graphing and Writing Linear Equations 4.1 5\" width=\"170\" height=\"283\" \/><br \/>\na. Graph the linear equation.<\/p>\n<p>Answer:<br \/>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-76016\" src=\"https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-Ideas-Math-Answers-8th-Grade-Chapter-4-img_14-300x242.png\" alt=\"Big Ideas Math Answers 8th Grade Chapter 4 img_14\" width=\"300\" height=\"242\" srcset=\"https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-Ideas-Math-Answers-8th-Grade-Chapter-4-img_14-300x242.png 300w, https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-Ideas-Math-Answers-8th-Grade-Chapter-4-img_14.png 625w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>b. You have $75 to spend. How many competitions can you attend?<br \/>\nAnswer:<br \/>\n75 \u2264 10x + 50<br \/>\n75 &#8211; 50 \u2264 10x<br \/>\n25 \u2264 10x<br \/>\n2.5 \u2265 x<br \/>\nBy this I can say that I can attend 2 competitions if I have $75 to spend.<\/p>\n<p>Question 15.<br \/>\nThe seating capacity for a banquet hall is represented by y = 8x + 56, where x is the number of extra tables you need. How many extra tables do you need to double the original seating capacity?<br \/>\nAnswer:<br \/>\nGiven,<br \/>\nThe seating capacity for a banquet hall is represented by y = 8x + 56, where x is the number of extra tables you need.<br \/>\ny = 8x + 56<br \/>\n2 \u00d7 56 = 8x + 56<br \/>\n112 = 8x + 56<br \/>\n8x = 112 &#8211; 56<br \/>\n8x = 56<br \/>\nx = 7 tables<\/p>\n<h3><a id=\"Graphing_Linear_Equations_Homework_&amp;_Practice_4.1\"><\/a>Graphing Linear Equations Homework &amp; Practice 4.1<\/h3>\n<p><strong>Review &amp; Refresh<\/strong><\/p>\n<p><strong>Tell whether the triangles are similar. Explain.<\/strong><br \/>\nQuestion 1.<br \/>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-32976\" src=\"https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-Ideas-Math-Answer-Key-Grade-8-Chapter-4-Graphing-and-Writing-Linear-Equations-4.1-6.png\" alt=\"Big Ideas Math Answer Key Grade 8 Chapter 4 Graphing and Writing Linear Equations 4.1 6\" width=\"198\" height=\"117\" \/><br \/>\nAnswer:<br \/>\nx\u00b0 + 46\u00b0 + 95\u00b0 = 180\u00b0<br \/>\nx\u00b0 + 141\u00b0 = 180\u00b0<br \/>\nx\u00b0 = 180\u00b0 &#8211; 141\u00b0<br \/>\nx\u00b0 = 39\u00b0<br \/>\nThus the angles of the triangle are 39\u00b0, 46\u00b0, 95\u00b0<br \/>\ny\u00b0 + 39\u00b0 + 46\u00b0 = 180\u00b0<br \/>\ny\u00b0 + 75\u00b0 = 180\u00b0<br \/>\ny\u00b0 = 180\u00b0 &#8211; 75\u00b0<br \/>\ny\u00b0 = 95\u00b0<br \/>\nThree angles of the triangle are 39\u00b0, 46\u00b0, 95\u00b0<br \/>\nThe triangles have two pairs of congruent angles.<\/p>\n<p>Question 2.<br \/>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-32977\" src=\"https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Big-Ideas-Math-Answer-Key-Grade-8-Chapter-4-Graphing-and-Writing-Linear-Equations-4.1-7.png\" alt=\"Big Ideas Math Answer Key Grade 8 Chapter 4 Graphing and Writing Linear Equations 4.1 7\" width=\"198\" height=\"123\" \/><br \/>\nAnswer:<br \/>\nx\u00b0 + 40\u00b0 + 51\u00b0 = 180\u00b0<br \/>\nx\u00b0 + 91\u00b0 = 180\u00b0<br \/>\nx\u00b0 = 180\u00b0 &#8211; 91\u00b0<br \/>\nx\u00b0 = 89\u00b0<br \/>\nThree angles of the triangle are 40\u00b0, 51\u00b0, 89\u00b0<br \/>\ny\u00b0 + 40\u00b0 + 79\u00b0 = 180\u00b0<br \/>\ny\u00b0 + 119\u00b0 = 180\u00b0<br \/>\ny\u00b0 = 180\u00b0 &#8211; 119\u00b0<br \/>\ny\u00b0 = 61\u00b0<\/p>\n<p><strong>Describe the translation of the point to its image.<\/strong><br \/>\nQuestion 3.<br \/>\n(1, &#8211; 4) \u2192 (3, 0)<br \/>\nAnswer:<br \/>\nA(1, -4) = A'(1 + 2, -4) = (3, -4)<br \/>\nA'(3, 4) = B(3, -4 + 4) = (3, 0)<br \/>\nTranslate 2 units right and 4 units up.<\/p>\n<p>Question 4.<br \/>\n(6, 4) \u2192 (- 4, &#8211; 6)<br \/>\nAnswer:<br \/>\nWe are given the points<br \/>\n(6, 4) \u2192 (- 4, &#8211; 6)<br \/>\nA(6, 4) = A'(6 &#8211; 10, 4) = (-4, 4)<br \/>\nA'(-4, -4) = B(-4, 4 &#8211; 10) = (-4, -6)<\/p>\n<p>Question 5.<br \/>\n(4, &#8211; 2) \u2192 (- 9, 3)<br \/>\nAnswer:<br \/>\nWe are given the points<br \/>\nA(4, -2)<br \/>\nB(-9, 3)<br \/>\nA(4, -2) = A'(4 &#8211; 13, -2) = (-9, -2)<br \/>\nA'(-9, -2) = B(-9, -2 + 4) = (-9, 3)<\/p>\n<p><strong>Concepts, Skills, &amp; Problem Solving<\/strong><\/p>\n<p><strong>CREATING GRAPHS<\/strong> Make a graph of the situation. (See Exploration 1, p. 141.)<br \/>\nQuestion 6.<br \/>\nThe equation y = &#8211; 2x + 8 represents the amount (in fluid ounces) of dish detergent in a bottle after x days of use.<br \/>\nAnswer:<br \/>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-76058\" src=\"https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Bigideas-math-answers-grade-8-chapter-4-img_15-294x300.png\" alt=\"Bigideas math answers grade 8 chapter 4 img_15\" width=\"294\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Bigideas-math-answers-grade-8-chapter-4-img_15-294x300.png 294w, https:\/\/ccssanswers.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Bigideas-math-answers-grade-8-chapter-4-img_15.png 699w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 294px) 100vw, 294px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Question 7.<br \/>\nThe equation y = 15x + 20 represents the cost (in dollars) of a gym membership after x months.<br \/>\nAnswer:<br \/>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-76060\" src=\"https:\/\/ccssanswers.com